               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1500" notAfter="1600">1500-1600</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Founded possibly during the time of King <persName ref="PRS8550sardaDe">Sarṣa Dǝngǝl</persName> (r. <date>1563–1597</date>).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gadām. It is still considered a monastery, but there are no monks. A small recent church dedicated to <persName ref="PRS10322Yemata">Yǝmʾātā</persName> is located on the other side of the road, on the rock, close to 
                     <placeName ref="INS0097AQG">ʿĀddi Qolqwāl (AQG)</placeName>. The church of <placeName ref="INS0039MY">Dabra Māʿṣo Yoḥannǝs</placeName> and it's flat-top mountain can be seen from the compound of Makāʿǝlo. &#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description"><figure>
                     <graphic url="Sites/MKMG.tif">
                        <desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</desc></graphic>
                  </figure>12 Mss photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg001">MKMG-001</ref> “ Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg002">MKMG-002</ref> “ Prayer of Incense”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg003">MKMG-003</ref> “ Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg004">MKMG-004</ref> “ Synaxarion (September-February)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg005">MKMG-005</ref> “Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg006">MKMG-006</ref> “ Miracles of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg007">MKMG-007</ref> “Vita of  Zä-Mikaʾel Arägawi”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg008">MKMG-008</ref> “ The Book of Baptism”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg009">MKMG-009</ref> “ Synaxarion (March-February)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg010">MKMG-010</ref> “ The Rite of the Holy Week”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg011">MKMG-011</ref> “The Book of Gǝṣṣǝw”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg012">MKMG-012</ref> “Miracles of Mary”.</ab>
      
